1.4.9. Week1 > Getting started > Step By Step Guideline for Opening a Text Editor



Step 1.  Open the Python IDLE

Step 2.  Select "File" and then click "New File"

An empty Text editor will appear

Step 3.  Select "File" and click on "Save" in order to save your file

Step 4.   Give a name to your file and remember that the extension should be .py

Step 5.  Now you can write a simple program. Simply write 

print(2+3) in your text editor. Then you can                          either F5 or Select "Run" and click on "Run Module" 

As you can see, the answer (5) will appear in your Python IDLE



